translated: Lundqvist, Märta, nurse, doctor, Gothenburg, born on 3/10/92 in Stockholm, daughter of G. V. L. and Amanda Edman. - graduated from high school in 1912, completed medical studies in 1915 and received a medical license in 1921, all in Stockholm. Studied abroad in Paris in 1928. Worked as an assistant doctor at Svenshögen's sanatorium in 1919, temporary senior assistant doctor at Högbo tuberculosis hospital in 1920, assistant doctor at Kålltorp tuberculosis hospital from 1921-1924, including three months as acting head doctor. Assistant doctor at St. Erik's hospital and nursing home from 1924-1925, temporary assistant doctor at Sabbatsberg hospital's medical department in 1925, substitute doctor in Sollebrunn, Svenljunga, and Tidaholm districts for shorter periods in 1925-1926, senior assistant doctor at Karlstad hospital's medical department from 1926-1927, and head assistant doctor there from 1927-1930. Has been working as a practicing doctor in Gothenburg since 1930.
